u}=m_{\pi}\quad\Longrightarrow\quad \sqrt{p^{2}+m_{\mu}^{2}}+p=m_{\pi}. \] Solving for \(p\), \[ p= rac{m_{\pi}^{2}-m_{\mu}^{2}}{2m_{\pi}}. \] Insert the masses (in MeV): \[ m_{\pi}=139.6,\qquad m_{\mu}=105.7, \] \[ p= rac{139.6^{2}-105.7^{2}}{2	imes139.6} = rac{19488.16-11172.49}{279.2} \approx 29.8\ 	ext{MeV}. \] Thus the neutrino kinetic energy (its total energy) is \[ K_{
